                                         "text":  "### An interdisciplinary study\n\n#### An overview\n\nThe study of geography is not completely independent of other areas. To begin with, there is the fact that, if planets exist, then it is necessary to analyze the knowledge that astrophysics brings us about how they are created.\n\nFrom the moment we need physics, we also begin to need mathematics, which is the language of nature.\n\nAs we progress, we will encounter political divisions created by humanity, which do not necessarily reflect divisions that existed billions of years before the Earth was formed.\n\nGiven this entire scenario, whenever necessary, we will first present knowledge from other areas, before finally entering into the content necessary to understand the atlas. Furthermore, in the texts we will also add references that will allow us to understand the contents of each page.\n\n#### Physics\n\nAs a first step, we will study, through physics, the formation of the universe and the planets.",
